## Get stats for an app

```
Definition
```

```http
GET /v3/apps/:guid/stats HTTP/1.1
```

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.[your-domain.com]/v3/apps/[guid]/stats" \
  -X GET \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]"
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK

{
  "processes": [
    {
      "type": "web",
      "index": 0,
      "state": "RUNNING",
      "usage": {
        "time": "2016-03-23T23:17:30.476314154Z",
        "cpu": 0.00038711029163348665,
        "mem": 19177472,
        disk": 69705728
      },
      "host": "10.244.16.10",
      "port": 60040,
      "uptime": 9042,
      "mem_quota": 268435456,
      "disk_quota": 1073741824,
      "fds_quota": 16384
    }
  ]
}
```

This endpoint retrieves the stats for all proceses of an app. See the <%= link_to "process stats object", "#the-process-stats-object" %> for more details.
